{
  "stem": "4830.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he said that all this anti-Jewish manifestations of Hitler, once they have their victory, will cease, and he will find a solution for the Jews that will be satisfactory to all these horrible measures, trying to reassure me.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But he was a good friend because I could discuss this with him.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Vadla Joseph Vadla.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But he was completely mesmerized by the German propaganda.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Even when we met after the siege of Budapest, when the Russian occupied Budapest-- in the middle of April, the schools reopened, and we met in the schools again.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I told him, you see?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he told me, just wait.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Still the new weapons may come.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This was in the middle of April.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But, of course, fortunately, they did not.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We remained friends, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As far as-- this conversation was after the-- after the-- after our part of the war.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The war wasn't finished yet, but as far as we were concerned, Hungary was already liberated by the Russian, so the war was over for us.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, he was-- he was-- You know, on one occasion, I had a temporary escape from my paramilitary unit, and on my way back, the rail was-- railway was cut by Allied bombers, and I couldn't go any further.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was stuck in a small suburb of Budapest, where he lived.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was very dangerous-- although I had some papers-- dangerous to stay in the station overnight.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I went to his house and asked him if I could stay with him for a night, and he was very accommodating.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He said that, of course, and he will go out of his bed and just-- because I don't have that opportunity, and I sleep there.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But this only lasted 20 minutes.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
